               <history>
                  <origin>
                     
                     <origDate notBefore="1892" notAfter="1913">Copying date: Production unit I. Text I was written probably in the reign of King Mǝnilǝk II (1892-1913); Text II was written later,  but not before 27 October 1916 (mentioned on fol. 12ra), and on the parchment leaves from the same batch that was used for Text I. Production unit II. Texts III-VI were written in the reign of King Mǝnilǝk II (1892-1913) who is mentioned on fol. 29v.</origDate>
                  </origin><provenance>The commissioners of Text I were Gabra Yoḥannǝs and Gabra Giyorgis, both mentioned extensively in the texts. In Text III, Gabra Māryām is mentioned as the father of the unnamed commissioner or scribe (fol. <locus target="#16v"/>).</provenance>
               </history>
               
               
